Which is your latest gadget? Samsung Galaxy Grand Prime Plus What do you love about it? The fact that it has not being stolen nor broken yet. It’s officially my longest serving phone at 7 months How does it help in your work? I need not visit a cyber café so that’s dope. Which of your gadgets wouldn’t you trade for anything? My Timberland watch. Your worst gadget ever and why? I once had a slide phone that was frequently turning blue whenever I texted. I got so frustrated with it that I threw it against the wall, breaking it into pieces. Which among your gadgets do you value the most? My watch. My husband bought it for me since I kept taking his. Which is your most expensive gadget and how much did it cost? Goodness, I cannot say I own expensive gadgets, maybe the watch, which was around 34k. Which gadget do you use the most and why? My phone. Instagram, Emails and phone calls. It is literally my laptop on the move. Which app do you use mostly on your phone and why? Instagram, because I am a social media freak. What would you be if you were a gadget? A humidifier. It’s quite refreshing to the mind and body. The gadget you can’t live without and why? My phone. It’s literally the most efficient tool of communication. I don’t know what I would do without it even for half a day. I would be completely lost. f you were to upgrade one of your most valued gadgets, what would you opt for and why? A Samsung S9. It has everything I would want in a phone. While shopping for gadgets, do you look for brands or its output? Both actually. The gadget you always wish you had? Honestly, a 6-burner cooker. Is that even a gadget?